If that quest has been completed, or failed, you will be unable to exit and re-enter Parphád in order to complete this quest.</rgb>

Upon entering Parphád, it is clear that the invaders here have little respect for these ruins. They haphazardly move about, toppling relics and damaging ancient texts.

You should take it upon yourself to reprimand the invaders for their clear disrespect of history.

<rgb=#FF0000>Warning: This quest requires Parphád: Order of Magnitude to be underway in order to access Parphád. If that quest has been completed, or failed, you will be unable to exit and re-enter Parphád in order to complete this quest.</rgb>
'Well done. I know that scholarly pursuits may not be to everyone's tastes, but even a warrior can respect what has come before.'
You should defeat enemies within Parphád and spare the ruins further damage.
You should speak with Ascbert and inform him of your efforts in preventing further damage to Parphád's relics.
Have you killed all the monsters yet?
